message.content: cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI. This paper deals with the problem of detecting duplicate questions in forums, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (LG), which makes cs.IR and cs.LG likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper uses adversarial domain adaptation, which is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence (AI) research, making cs.AI a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with forum data, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
